    "title": {
        "rendered": "ColorIndicator"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>ColorIndicator is a React component that renders a specific color in a circle. It&#8217;s often used to summarize a collection of used colors in a child component.</p>\n<h3>Single component</h3>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/user-images.githubusercontent.com/881729/147558034-cba09db5-2f06-458b-a7b1-fd2f2ffb982a.png?ssl=1\" alt=\"simple color indicator\" /></p>\n<h3>Used in sidebar</h3>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/user-images.githubusercontent.com/881729/147559177-69ce52e1-30dc-4f24-8483-ca2a580f434f.png?ssl=1\" alt=\"multiple color indicator\" /></p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">import { ColorIndicator } from '@wordpress/components';\n\nconst MyColorIndicator = () =&gt; &lt;ColorIndicator colorValue=\"#0073aa\" /&gt;;\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Props</h2>\n<p>The component accepts the following props:</p>\n<h3><code>className</code>: <code>string</code></h3>\n<p>Extra classes for the used <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> element. By default only <code>component-color-indicator</code> is added.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Required: No</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><code>colorValue</code>: <code>CSSProperties[ 'background' ]</code></h3>\n<p>The color of the indicator. Any value from the CSS <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background\"><code>background</code></a> property is supported.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Required: Yes</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
